88.0	Social_democracy	Social democracy	Social democracy is officially a reformist democratic socialist political ideology. Social democracy supports a social welfare state based upon publicly-funded social welfare, that supports legal entitlements in social rights for citizens to universal access to public services such as: workers' compensation, universal health care and universal education, and other services such as child care and care for the elderly. Social democracy is connected with the trade union labour movement and supports collective bargaining rights for workers. Contemporary social democracy advocates freedom from discrimination based on differences of: ability/disability, age, class, ethnicity, gender, language, race, religion, and sexual orientation. Most social democratic parties are affiliated with the Socialist International.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Red_rose_02_-.jpg.svg/100px-Red_rose_02_-.jpg.svg.png
